[This is the 2nd part of the daily update following the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic, with a focus on selected countries of interest.

To reduce the size of these posts, there will be changes over the coming days. The tables will be reduced but are available at the source URLs and will be referred to in the summaries of daily changes for each country. Countries that have almost interrupted transmission and have been lifting restrictions (China, South Korea) and have lessons to learn as they attempt to prevent explosive 2nd waves will continue to be profiled. We will attempt to select countries from each region on a daily basis. - Mod.UBA]

In this update:
[1] China: National Health Commission, 83 057 total cases, 4634 deaths
[2] South Korea: 11 947 confirmed cases, 276 deaths
[3] Italy: 236 142 total cases, 34 167 deaths
[4] Iran: 177 938 total cases, 8506 deaths
[5] USA: 2 066 401 total cases, 115 130 deaths

