[1] China: National Health Commission, 83 057 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Wed 10 Jun 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in English, abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-06/11/c_80725.htm


On [10 Jun 2020]:
- 11 new cases of confirmed infection (all imported cases, 6 in Shanghai municipality, 3 in Guangdong province, 1 in Tianjin municipality, and 1 in Fujian province), no new suspected cases, and no new deaths. Also, 4 patients were released from hospital after being cured; 358 people who had had close contact with infected patients were freed from medical observation.
- 1797 [total] cases of imported confirmed infections and no deaths.
- The National Health Commission had received reports of 83 057 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 361 patients had been cured and discharged from hospital; 750 487 people have been identified as having had close contact with infected patients; 3179 are now under medical observation.
- 4 new asymptomatic cases (3 imported); 1 asymptomatic case became a confirmed case; 129 asymptomatic cases were still under medical observation (including 45 imported cases).
- 1595 confirmed infections had been reported in the Hong Kong, Macau special administrative regions and Taiwan province: 1107 in Hong Kong, 45 in Macau, 443 in Taiwan.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to the report above, in the past 24 hours, there have been 11 newly confirmed cases in China, all imported. No new deaths were reported. Also, no new cases were reported in Hong Kong or in Macau. A total of 1797 imported cases have been reported. There have been no new deaths reported for several weeks, further supporting a reduced level of cases in the country.

There were 4 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals in the past 24 hours, 3 of which were imported. There was 1 case of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. The recent previous reports of a conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic were on 4, 6, and 8 Jun 2020 when 1 conversion was reported each time. Prior to that, there were 2 cases on 1 Jun 2020, and a single case was reported on 18 May 2020 (COVID-19 update (194): China, S Korea, countries w/ high local trans, Italy phase 2 20200519.7352327).

Recurrent questions: What is the total number of asymptomatic cases? What is the total number of asymptomatic cases that converted to symptomatic? What is the proportion of asymptomatic imported cases that have been linked to transmission chains resulting in outbreak clusters?

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7459205,155. - Mod.UBA]

